[{'date': {'start': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'role': 'Young Professional Advisor', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'United Europe e.V.', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4E0BAQEugy0yZ6wL3Q/company-logo_400_400/0/1640256131688?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=3GCeMkGVP5JADqMV4X9mhEvueq96FfCxobk3Ok5-0Hw', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/united-europe-ev/'}, 'cause': 'POLITICS', 'description': 'The Young Professional Advisors are a group of more than 40 United Europe alumni from over 20 European countries. The network promotes professional exchanges between young Europeans on topics such as democracy, healthcare, economics, digitisation, and security whilst also encouraging impulses for a more European way of thinking.
The platform provides an exchange of views and insights about diverse perspectives on the future of Europe and makes Young Professional opinions more visible. The YPAs aim is to restore trust in the European project among the youth and citizens of Europe and to generate forward-looking ideas for smart analysis of EU policies. https://www.united-europe.eu/young-professional-advisors/'}, {'date': {'start': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'role': 'Fundraising Cyclist', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Team Rynkeby Deutschland', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/D4E0BAQFqShSSovaJAw/company-logo_400_400/0/1666084153649?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=sN3QSMYcyPnnZlsH_hW5r6-JF03bOK2ObIeK5KGuM5w', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/team-rynkeby-germany/'}, 'cause': 'CHILDREN', 'description': "Team Rynkeby is a Nordic charity cycling team. Every summer we cycle to Paris to raise money for seriously ill children.

Team Rynkeby was founded in 2002, when 11 amateur cyclists associated with Rynkeby Foods A/S decided to cycle to Paris to see the final stage of the Tour de France.

Rynkeby Foods was the main sponsor of their trip, which was also backed by other companies. In fact, the cyclists who joined the world's first Team Rynkeby team were so accomplished at finding sponsors that, when the team returned to Denmark just over a week later, the team had made € 5,100 profit.

Today, Team Rynkeby comprises 2,400 cyclists and 550 volunteers, divided into 59 local teams from Denmark, Sweden, Finland, Norway, the Faroe Islands, Germany and Switzerland. 

Team members are selected from thousands of applicants, who have completed the application form on the Team Rynkeby website.
Read more here: https://www.teamrynkeby-hohesc.de/

The new season has started, which will see its hightlight with the ride to Paris in July 2021. 
If you want to support this tremendous effort for children's health - every single Euro is donated - please send me message."}]
